📘 Day 28 – DATABASE (Complete Foundation Notes)

---

 1️⃣ What is Data?

Tumne likha tha:

Information → Knowledge → Fact → Data

Let’s clarify properly:

 ✅ Data

Raw facts & figures without context.

Example:

 101
 Ayush
 50000
 01/01/2026

Ye sirf raw values hain.

---

 ✅ Information

Processed data that has meaning.

Example:
Salary = ₹50,000
Employee Name = Ayush

---

 ✅ Knowledge

Understanding patterns from information.

Example:
If salary increased → Performance good.

---

 2️⃣ What is a Database?

Database = Organized collection of data.

Simple words:
👉 Data ko structured tarike se store karna taaki easily retrieve ho sake.

Example:
Bank system me:

 Customer details
 Account balance
 Transactions

Ye sab database me stored hota hai.

---

 3️⃣ What is DBMS? (Database Management System)

DBMS = Software jo database ko manage karta hai.

Tumne likha tha:

 Data store
 Data dikhata
 Update
 Delete

Yes ✅
Ye sab DBMS karta hai.

 DBMS ke functions:

✔ Store data
✔ Retrieve data
✔ Update data
✔ Delete data
✔ Security control
✔ Backup & recovery
✔ Multi-user access

---

 4️⃣ Real-World Industry Example

 Example: Flipkart

Jab tum product search karte ho:

→ Product data database se fetch hota hai
→ Price update hota hai
→ Stock update hota hai
→ Order insert hota hai

Ye sab DBMS handle karta hai.

---

 5️⃣ Types of DBMS

Tumhare diagram ke according 👇

---

 1️⃣ RDBMS (Relational DBMS)

Structure:
→ Tables (Rows + Columns)
→ Relation between tables

Example:
Students Table
Courses Table

Relation:
Student_ID → Foreign key

---

 Real-World Example:

Banking System
E-commerce
ERP systems

---

 Popular RDBMS:

 MySQL
 PostgreSQL
 Oracle
 SQL Server

---

 AWS Example:

→ Amazon RDS
→ Aurora

---

 2️⃣ NoSQL / Non-Relational DBMS

No fixed table structure.

Types:

 Key-Value
 Document
 Column
 Graph

Used when:
→ Large scale data
→ High speed
→ Flexible schema

---

 Real-World Example:

Instagram
Netflix
Amazon recommendations

---

 AWS Example:

→ DynamoDB

---

 3️⃣ ODBMS (Object-Oriented DBMS)

Data stored as objects (like programming objects).

Use case:
→ When application built using OOP languages

Less common in industry compared to RDBMS & NoSQL.

---

 4️⃣ Network DBMS

Structure like graph/network.

Used for:
→ Complex many-to-many relationships

Modern version:
→ Graph databases

Example:
Social media friend connections.

---

 5️⃣ Cloud-Based DBMS

Database hosted on cloud infrastructure.

Benefits:
✔ High availability
✔ Scalability
✔ Automatic backup
✔ Managed service

---

 AWS Examples:

→ RDS
→ Aurora
→ DynamoDB
→ Redshift

Industry me mostly Cloud DB use hota hai.

---

 6️⃣ Difference Between DBMS Types

| Feature   | RDBMS    | NoSQL      | ODBMS        |
| --------- | -------- | ---------- | ------------ |
| Structure | Tables   | Flexible   | Objects      |
| Schema    | Fixed    | Dynamic    | Object-based |
| Scale     | Vertical | Horizontal | Moderate     |
| Use Case  | Banking  | Big data   | OOP apps     |

---

 7️⃣ SQL (Structured Query Language)

Tumhare diagram ke according 👇

SQL Categories:

 1️⃣ DDL (Data Definition Language)

→ CREATE
→ DROP
→ ALTER

Structure define karta hai.

---

 2️⃣ DML (Data Manipulation Language)

→ INSERT
→ UPDATE
→ DELETE

Data modify karta hai.

---

 3️⃣ DQL (Data Query Language)

→ SELECT

Data fetch karta hai.

---

 4️⃣ DCL (Data Control Language)

→ GRANT
→ REVOKE

Permissions manage karta hai.

---

 5️⃣ TCL (Transaction Control Language)

→ COMMIT
→ ROLLBACK

Transaction control karta hai.

